police-involved deaths

data source: US Police Involved Fatalities

The data set represents data from the years 2000 through 2016, representing 12,491 police-involved deaths across the United States.

reported circumstances

human details

The age range represented in the data set is from 1 to 107. The average age is 35.

The people represented in the data were 95.1% males. Gender was unspecified for 0.064% of the people represented.

u.s. national trend
